items.name: MessageUI-ContactsUI-Framework
items.description: An application that uses a UINavigationController to display a MFMailComposeViewController, CNContactPickerViewController, and CNContactViewController. The main view displays two buttons and a UITableView. One button displays the CNContactPickerViewController. This controller will display all the devices contacts, tapping a contact will display the contact details. If this contact has an email address, tapping it will open an MFMailComposeViewController with the intended recipient already loaded in. The other button on the main view will display the CNContactViewController (new contact), allowing the user to add a new contact. The UITableView on the main page will have an entry for each email sent. Canceled emails are not included in this list. The data thats stored is the intended recipient and a timestamp of when it was sent.
